<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-08-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-08-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="21" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d21">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName type="from">Churchill</persName> to President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d21fn1">Sent to
                                Washington by the United States Military Attaché, London, via Army
                                channels; forwarded by the White House Map Room to Roosevelt, who
                                was then in Alaska, as telegram No. <gloss target="#t_Red1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Red</hi></gloss> 265.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-08">8 August 1944</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Prime Minister to President Roosevelt. Personal and top secret. Number
                            746.</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>I will certainly come to Bermuda at any time. We could make you
                                very comfortable at Government House. I had preparations made some
                                months ago for your personal convenience in every way. Whatever you
                                wish in these matters will be agreeable to us.</item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>By “climax” I did not mean “end”.</item>
                            <label>3.</label>
                            <item>Thank you for your very kind personal thoughts.</item>
                        </list>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>